Build Instructions
Requirements
Software
Android Studio Hedgehog or newer
JDK 17
Android SDK 35
Gradle 8+
Clone Repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/TravelCopilot.git
cd TravelCopilot
Configure Local Secrets

Create:

local.properties

Add:

MAPS_API_KEY=YOUR_KEY
OPENAI_API_KEY=YOUR_KEY

Do NOT commit this file.

Build Debug APK
./gradlew assembleDebug
Run Unit Tests
./gradlew test
Install to Device
./gradlew installDebug
Permissions Required

TravelCopilot requires the following Android permissions.

Permission	Purpose
RECORD_AUDIO	Voice interaction
ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION	GPS tracking
ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION	General location
FOREGROUND_SERVICE	Background assistant service
POST_NOTIFICATIONS	Foreground service notifications
INTERNET	AI provider access
WAKE_LOCK	Long-running assistant operation
State Machine Architecture

TravelCopilot uses deterministic state machines for:

trip lifecycle,
voice interaction,
assistant orchestration,
service lifecycle,
and recovery behavior.

See:

docs/STATE_MACHINE.md
Database Architecture

The application uses Room as the authoritative persistence layer.

Core persistence domains include:

trips,
events,
conversations,
memory,
route history,
and summaries.

See:

docs/DATABASE_SCHEMA.md
